1
00:00:08,109 --> 00:00:11,580
Starting today, I’ll be taking
on the role of your secretary.

2
00:00:12,410 --> 00:00:13,180
Listen.

3
00:00:13,610 --> 00:00:15,130
I don't need a secretary.

4
00:00:15,240 --> 00:00:16,320
I can't do that either.

5
00:00:16,490 --> 00:00:20,550
I have a contract with your father, and
I’m not risking a breach of contract suit.

6
00:00:20,580 --> 00:00:22,800
We’ll see about that, Aran.

7
00:00:23,200 --> 00:00:25,140
Do you think I'm doing a good job, Khun Lené?

8
00:00:25,420 --> 00:00:29,630
Good enough to be the one by
your side instead of Khun Peem?

9
00:00:29,770 --> 00:00:31,240
Do you even know who he is?

10
00:00:31,590 --> 00:00:33,930
I’m Peem. Nice to meet you.

11
00:00:34,030 --> 00:00:35,370
And do you?

12
00:00:35,470 --> 00:00:36,650
Don't talk back to me.

13
00:00:36,820 --> 00:00:39,320
I told you already, didn't I?
Get out of my sight!

14
00:00:39,860 --> 00:00:43,000
I used to be your P’ Le,
but that’s not the case anymore.

15
00:00:44,310 --> 00:00:47,670
Why did you come back, Rann,
when I pushed you away so hard?

16
00:01:07,870 --> 00:01:09,900
I’ve kicked you out of my life once before.

17
00:01:10,880 --> 00:01:14,910
What makes you think… I can't do it again?

18
00:02:13,320 --> 00:02:15,600
Was what I did really that unforgivable, P’ Le?

19
00:02:15,950 --> 00:02:18,700
Why do you have to be so mean to me?

20
00:02:41,770 --> 00:02:42,980
Why did you come back?

21
00:02:44,100 --> 00:02:46,230
Push me away all you want,
but I'm not going anywhere.

22
00:02:46,530 --> 00:02:48,370
I’m going to save you, no matter what.

23
00:03:26,010 --> 00:03:28,300
Aran Kretkaew

24
00:03:36,050 --> 00:03:40,310
Scholarship Award Confirmation for Aran Kretkaew

25
00:03:42,940 --> 00:03:46,660
Funded by Ledarin Asawachun

26
00:03:55,930 --> 00:03:57,560
This entire scholarship...

27
00:04:00,920 --> 00:04:02,420
it was P' Le all along?

28
00:04:20,390 --> 00:04:21,940
Why would you do this?

29
00:04:35,840 --> 00:04:39,870
If you cared... then that day...

30
00:04:43,300 --> 00:04:45,210
Why did you have to drive me away?

31
00:07:04,910 --> 00:07:07,290
P’ Le, I found out about the scholarship.

32
00:07:08,310 --> 00:07:09,590
Why did you do this?

33
00:07:10,420 --> 00:07:12,310
Just ask her, Rann. You have to ask.

34
00:07:12,960 --> 00:07:14,860
You need to hear the reason from her own lips.

35
00:07:20,680 --> 00:07:21,430
P’ Le.

36
00:07:27,950 --> 00:07:29,260
Who said you could call me that?

37
00:07:30,530 --> 00:07:31,480
I’m sorry.

38
00:07:33,060 --> 00:07:33,970
Khun Lené.

39
00:07:36,240 --> 00:07:37,600
Can I ask you something?

40
00:07:38,720 --> 00:07:39,500
What?

41
00:07:41,330 --> 00:07:42,340
Um…

42
00:07:45,560 --> 00:07:47,440
I don’t have all day for you.

43
00:07:47,920 --> 00:07:49,940
Let's go. We're wasting time.

44
00:07:51,290 --> 00:07:52,730
- Wait a second! Oh!
- Khun Rann!

45
00:08:08,520 --> 00:08:10,710
Clumsy. Watch your step.

46
00:08:11,060 --> 00:08:12,820
If you trip like that at the company,

47
00:08:12,850 --> 00:08:15,190
people will think my
secretary isn't professional.

48
00:08:15,290 --> 00:08:18,860
I’m sorry. I’ll be more careful from now on.

49
00:08:20,050 --> 00:08:22,790
- And thank you—
- Go get Khun Rann a new pair of shoes.

50
00:08:23,430 --> 00:08:24,430
Yes, Khun Lené.

51
00:08:26,500 --> 00:08:27,510
Your bag.

52
00:08:30,300 --> 00:08:31,100
P’ Le.

53
00:08:39,080 --> 00:08:40,309
Your shoes, Khun Rann.

54
00:08:42,919 --> 00:08:43,900
Thank you.

55
00:08:46,920 --> 00:08:49,250
- There you go.
- Thank you, P’ Dia.

56
00:08:51,570 --> 00:08:54,380
Do you know why Khun Lené
changed her car, Khun Rann?

57
00:09:02,670 --> 00:09:04,250
Think about it carefully.

58
00:09:09,890 --> 00:09:10,900
I don’t understand.

59
00:09:12,070 --> 00:09:14,900
You should hurry.
Don't keep Khun Lené waiting any longer.

60
00:09:15,330 --> 00:09:16,900
- Off you go.
- Okay?

61
00:09:17,280 --> 00:09:18,280
Chop-chop.

62
00:09:30,450 --> 00:09:31,530
It’s true.

63
00:09:34,930 --> 00:09:37,340
Hey, you feel that?
Something is definitely off.

64
00:09:38,320 --> 00:09:40,870
It's a silent storm, I’m telling you.

65
00:09:41,010 --> 00:09:44,050
They look calm, but the energy
coming off them is sub-zero.

66
00:09:44,080 --> 00:09:45,380
It’s rattling the whole office.

67
00:09:45,630 --> 00:09:46,810
Can a storm even be silent?

68
00:09:53,990 --> 00:09:55,280
Oh, Khun Rann.

69
00:09:55,730 --> 00:09:57,990
Here’s the product list from our last meeting.

70
00:09:58,330 --> 00:09:59,240
Thank you.

71
00:10:02,270 --> 00:10:03,190
Khun Peem.

72
00:10:05,180 --> 00:10:07,230
What’s with the tension between them?

73
00:10:08,940 --> 00:10:11,000
Looks like a Cold War to me.

74
00:10:13,460 --> 00:10:17,610
Oh, I almost forgot. Khun Kanin is
waiting for you in your office, Khun Lené.

75
00:10:25,610 --> 00:10:27,680
I’ll look into the products myself.

76
00:10:29,060 --> 00:10:31,500
Tell the warehouse manager
I’ll be stopping by today.

77
00:10:37,390 --> 00:10:39,450
Stay here.
I won't be needing any notes for this.

78
00:10:43,680 --> 00:10:44,680
See you in a bit.

79
00:10:46,180 --> 00:10:48,990
Sis, I don’t think it’s a Cold War anymore.

80
00:10:49,460 --> 00:10:50,970
That’s a total apocalypse.

81
00:10:51,220 --> 00:10:52,260
No kidding.

82
00:10:52,340 --> 00:10:56,550
You guys better get ready.
Once they’re done talking...

83
00:10:56,570 --> 00:10:58,700
- It's brace for impact time?
- Exactly.

84
00:11:11,090 --> 00:11:12,100
You’re finally here.

85
00:11:14,540 --> 00:11:17,970
Is there something you need
that brings you here so early, Dad?

86
00:11:20,280 --> 00:11:25,690
Well, I just wanted to ask you one more time...

87
00:11:27,220 --> 00:11:28,820
Are you sure you won't change your mind?

88
00:11:30,680 --> 00:11:31,680
About what?

89
00:11:33,920 --> 00:11:35,400
Is that how we're going to play this?

90
00:11:41,270 --> 00:11:42,500
Fine, fine, fine.

91
00:11:44,260 --> 00:11:47,490
I’m talking about the new
shareholder we're bringing in.

92
00:11:48,430 --> 00:11:53,900
I’m planning to introduce him to
the Board of Directors at the next meeting.

93
00:11:55,360 --> 00:11:59,070
Isn't it a little early for that?
I thought it was still under discussion.

94
00:12:02,220 --> 00:12:03,940
That’s just what you think, dear.

95
00:12:08,800 --> 00:12:12,460
If you’ve already decided,
then I have no reason to argue.

96
00:12:13,780 --> 00:12:14,650
Good.

97
00:12:15,900 --> 00:12:18,900
In that case, I’m trusting you to look after him.

98
00:12:20,680 --> 00:12:23,050
With special care.
You understand, don’t you?

99
00:12:23,990 --> 00:12:27,440
Of course. I'll take excellent care of him.

100
00:12:32,460 --> 00:12:33,170
Oh.

101
00:12:35,110 --> 00:12:37,840
And how is the new secretary working out?
Is she to your liking?

102
00:12:44,470 --> 00:12:48,170
Since you chose her for me,
how could I not be satisfied?

103
00:12:49,260 --> 00:12:51,350
I only ever want the best for you.

104
00:12:56,020 --> 00:12:57,130
I’m off, then.

105
00:13:26,600 --> 00:13:27,490
Nong Rann.

106
00:13:30,540 --> 00:13:31,390
Nong Rann!

107
00:13:32,310 --> 00:13:34,800
Don't frown so much.
You’ll get wrinkles before your time.

108
00:13:35,540 --> 00:13:37,910
A pretty face like yours needs
to be maintained, after all.

109
00:13:41,180 --> 00:13:42,980
What's wrong? Come on, tell me.

110
00:13:46,460 --> 00:13:48,080
Can I ask you something?

111
00:13:48,420 --> 00:13:51,830
Who’s the fairest of them all!!!

112
00:13:54,100 --> 00:13:55,100
Okay, no jokes.

113
00:13:55,810 --> 00:13:56,940
Tell me what’s going on.

114
00:13:59,210 --> 00:14:01,020
Have you been working here long?

115
00:14:03,300 --> 00:14:04,310
Quite a few years now.

116
00:14:07,280 --> 00:14:10,910
Since the very first days Khun Lené started?

117
00:14:12,170 --> 00:14:12,970
No.

118
00:14:13,210 --> 00:14:16,310
Back then, I was still an engineering
girl screaming over factory boys.

119
00:14:17,270 --> 00:14:20,000
But if you really want the tea,
you have to ask that auntie.

120
00:14:20,290 --> 00:14:22,140
She’s been here since the dawn of time.

121
00:14:22,730 --> 00:14:23,900
Are you calling me old?

122
00:14:24,310 --> 00:14:25,320
When did you get here?

123
00:14:25,620 --> 00:14:26,520
Biatch.

124
00:14:27,330 --> 00:14:28,690
Wanna know about Khun Lené?

125
00:14:30,720 --> 00:14:32,550
You might not believe me,
but you know what?

126
00:14:32,570 --> 00:14:38,290
The greatest wonder of this office is that
Khun Lené used to be kind to everyone.

127
00:14:40,790 --> 00:14:42,220
You don't believe me?

128
00:14:42,250 --> 00:14:45,660
I don't know what kind of demon
possessed her either, but I was so scared.

129
00:14:45,960 --> 00:14:47,570
Especially on a day like today.

130
00:14:48,740 --> 00:14:49,710
So scary.

131
00:14:50,310 --> 00:14:52,780
That’s right. P’ Le used to be like that.

132
00:14:53,770 --> 00:14:56,040
Which means something really did happen here.

133
00:14:57,040 --> 00:14:58,100
Why is that?

134
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:00,950
Soon as she’s done with her dad, she’s out.

135
00:15:00,970 --> 00:15:02,820
She spikes, she digs, she swings, she blocks.

136
00:15:02,860 --> 00:15:04,660
Door slams—BAM! Files hurled—BOOM!

137
00:15:04,680 --> 00:15:05,540
We all get the message.

138
00:15:05,560 --> 00:15:08,810
You might get caught in the crossfire,
so they’re worried about you.

139
00:15:14,660 --> 00:15:15,930
Sawasdee ka, Khun Kanin.

140
00:15:25,780 --> 00:15:27,130
Take care of Lené for me, Rann.

141
00:15:28,300 --> 00:15:29,760
Of course, Khun Kanin.

142
00:15:51,920 --> 00:15:53,140
Sawasdee krub, Khun Lené.

143
00:15:53,820 --> 00:15:54,830
What’s the situation?

144
00:15:55,360 --> 00:15:58,960
As I reported before, the
special shipment we brought in…

145
00:15:59,260 --> 00:16:01,400
some items don't match the purchase order again.

146
00:16:04,390 --> 00:16:05,960
We’ve double-checked everything.

147
00:16:06,480 --> 00:16:10,250
The error likely occurred during the final
transit before reaching the warehouse.

148
00:16:10,670 --> 00:16:14,610
We’re currently cross-referencing to see
which other items don't match the system.

149
00:16:17,080 --> 00:16:20,230
Separate everything that doesn't
match the list and show me the way.

150
00:16:20,440 --> 00:16:22,240
Certainly. This way, please.

151
00:16:26,130 --> 00:16:28,080
No. You wait here.

152
00:16:33,330 --> 00:16:34,220
You too.

153
00:16:43,910 --> 00:16:45,720
You’re caught in the crossfire this time too.

154
00:16:48,870 --> 00:16:51,120
I guess the Cold War is escalating.

155
00:17:04,220 --> 00:17:05,700
Excuse me, I have to take this call.

156
00:17:07,160 --> 00:17:08,170
By all means.

157
00:17:25,790 --> 00:17:28,240
Khun Lené is checking
the special shipment right now.

158
00:17:29,600 --> 00:17:31,000
She doesn't suspect a thing.

159
00:17:31,140 --> 00:17:33,520
Don't worry, she’s still in the dark.

160
00:17:34,550 --> 00:17:37,490
I'll be keeping an eye on her and
make sure she doesn't cross the line.

161
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:39,010
Who is he reporting to?

162
00:17:39,640 --> 00:17:40,570
Understood.

163
00:17:57,850 --> 00:17:58,830
P’ Le.

164
00:17:59,680 --> 00:18:01,210
Didn't I tell you to wait over there?

165
00:18:01,870 --> 00:18:04,730
I need to speak with you.
It’s really important.

166
00:18:11,470 --> 00:18:12,300
Follow me.

167
00:18:20,410 --> 00:18:21,510
Get straight to the point.

168
00:18:24,390 --> 00:18:27,000
I know I shouldn’t be saying this.

169
00:18:31,070 --> 00:18:32,810
But I'm feeling uneasy about Khun Peem.

170
00:18:37,140 --> 00:18:38,140
He…

171
00:18:40,550 --> 00:18:42,800
might not be someone you should trust.

172
00:18:45,360 --> 00:18:46,490
Watch your words.

173
00:18:47,430 --> 00:18:49,330
You’re making accusations
against my bodyguard.

174
00:18:49,510 --> 00:18:53,390
I know I don't have any proof,
and I don’t want to accuse anyone,

175
00:18:53,760 --> 00:18:55,120
but I overheard him on the phone.

176
00:19:02,170 --> 00:19:04,640
He was reporting on you to someone.

177
00:19:06,190 --> 00:19:07,750
I want you to stay on your guard.

178
00:19:10,740 --> 00:19:12,400
First you wanted his job.

179
00:19:13,920 --> 00:19:15,430
Now you’re trying to frame him?

180
00:19:16,780 --> 00:19:20,660
I don’t know why you’ve
decided to show your face again.

181
00:19:21,690 --> 00:19:25,350
But between a bodyguard I’ve always trusted

182
00:19:25,820 --> 00:19:29,170
and you—someone my father hired—

183
00:19:29,750 --> 00:19:31,630
who do you honestly think I should trust more?

184
00:19:36,220 --> 00:19:41,130
Shouldn't I be more worried that you’re
the one reporting on me to someone?

185
00:19:41,220 --> 00:19:43,990
- No! I would never—
- You’re just a secretary.

186
00:19:46,160 --> 00:19:47,790
Don’t overstep your bounds.

187
00:20:13,390 --> 00:20:14,390
P’ Le.

188
00:20:22,870 --> 00:20:25,180
Is anyone hungry?
Would you like to stop for a bite first?

189
00:20:27,720 --> 00:20:30,550
People at the office say
there's a new place nearby.

190
00:20:30,920 --> 00:20:32,400
Apparently, the food is quite good.

191
00:20:36,860 --> 00:20:38,160
Thank you for the answer.

192
00:20:39,980 --> 00:20:41,820
Not so loud.
The silence is deafening.

193
00:20:42,460 --> 00:20:43,590
I’ll just go alone then.

194
00:21:09,110 --> 00:21:12,420
That was suffocating!
I’m about to lose my frickin’ mind.

195
00:21:15,920 --> 00:21:17,050
Wait, Khun Lené.

196
00:21:17,580 --> 00:21:18,580
What now?

197
00:21:21,040 --> 00:21:22,970
No matter how you feel about me,

198
00:21:24,080 --> 00:21:28,990
I’m asking you to please stay on your guard.

199
00:21:31,280 --> 00:21:32,280
Against what?

200
00:21:35,720 --> 00:21:37,170
- Against you?
- No!

201
00:21:38,990 --> 00:21:40,500
I would never hurt you.

202
00:21:43,940 --> 00:21:44,990
And I should believe you…

203
00:21:47,350 --> 00:21:48,540
just because you say so?

204
00:21:50,620 --> 00:21:52,000
Since we're on the subject...

205
00:21:53,440 --> 00:21:55,300
Why did you come back into my life?

206
00:21:57,020 --> 00:21:59,360
Who do you think you are to
be warning me about Peem?

207
00:22:00,380 --> 00:22:05,410
You're the one who forced yourself
into my work, into my home...

208
00:22:07,890 --> 00:22:09,630
when I never even wanted you there.

209
00:22:12,360 --> 00:22:16,170
Give me one good reason why
I should believe anything you say!

210
00:22:18,920 --> 00:22:22,050
I... I just want you to be safe.

211
00:22:22,080 --> 00:22:23,110
Safe from what?

212
00:22:25,350 --> 00:22:26,540
What have you heard?

213
00:22:29,320 --> 00:22:33,020
Or are you and my father actually
plotting something together?

214
00:22:35,080 --> 00:22:36,040
That's not true.

215
00:22:36,810 --> 00:22:38,440
I've never plotted anything with anyone.

216
00:22:39,440 --> 00:22:41,200
What does Khun Kanin have to do with this?

217
00:22:42,770 --> 00:22:44,180
I’m just truly worried about you.

218
00:22:47,020 --> 00:22:48,220
Why would you be worried?!

219
00:22:49,630 --> 00:22:50,400
What?

220
00:22:52,270 --> 00:22:53,490
Is someone going to kill me?

221
00:23:01,990 --> 00:23:03,060
You guys didn’t know?

222
00:23:03,390 --> 00:23:05,740
I heard there were a lot
of strange things that night.

223
00:23:05,890 --> 00:23:08,880
There are rumors going around that Khun Lené got…

224
00:23:12,800 --> 00:23:13,650
Why are you silent?!

225
00:23:14,830 --> 00:23:17,440
Answer me! I asked what you’ve heard.

226
00:23:17,880 --> 00:23:19,950
What is it you really want from me, Rann?!

227
00:23:19,970 --> 00:23:21,910
I just don’t want to lose you again!

228
00:23:29,050 --> 00:23:30,310
You have no idea…

229
00:23:32,920 --> 00:23:34,540
what I’ve been through.

230
00:23:36,450 --> 00:23:37,700
You have no idea…

231
00:23:39,290 --> 00:23:40,880
what I’ve had to do...

232
00:23:42,040 --> 00:23:47,210
or how hard I’ve tried
just to stand by your side again!

233
00:23:54,400 --> 00:23:57,110
See? You're pushing me away again.

234
00:24:01,970 --> 00:24:04,200
You told me to get out of your sight.

235
00:24:06,370 --> 00:24:09,160
Then why do you still keep my picture?

236
00:24:13,620 --> 00:24:17,310
Weren’t you the one who
gave me that scholarship?

237
00:24:18,420 --> 00:24:20,340
You told me to get lost.

238
00:24:21,010 --> 00:24:23,380
So why did you keep taking care of me?

239
00:24:27,080 --> 00:24:31,160
Do you have any idea how terrified I am
that something will happen to you?

240
00:24:31,180 --> 00:24:34,590
How scared I am that I'll wake up
tomorrow and you won’t be there anymore?

241
00:24:40,430 --> 00:24:43,310
You're the one who knows nothing.

242
00:24:47,860 --> 00:24:48,710
Do you realize...

243
00:24:50,960 --> 00:24:51,880
what you’re saying?

244
00:24:52,540 --> 00:24:53,360
I do.

245
00:24:55,240 --> 00:24:56,950
I just want you to be sure...

246
00:24:59,750 --> 00:25:04,260
- that I would never hurt the person I—
- That’s enough.

247
00:25:04,280 --> 00:25:06,950
No. Please don't be like this.

248
00:25:08,220 --> 00:25:11,610
All this time... I’ve missed you.

249
00:25:12,680 --> 00:25:14,460
I’ve missed you so much.

250
00:25:16,400 --> 00:25:18,320
I've missed you all along.

251
00:25:18,780 --> 00:25:23,820
~ I can only look back on days
that have turned to dust ~

252
00:25:25,540 --> 00:25:31,540
~ A Time when I let you walk away ~

253
00:25:35,470 --> 00:25:38,680
~ Since the moment of my return ~

254
00:25:38,710 --> 00:25:41,850
~ I realized I came back for you ~

255
00:25:42,010 --> 00:25:44,690
~ I’ve come back to make things right ~

256
00:25:44,710 --> 00:25:48,580
~ For the day I left you all alone ~

257
00:25:48,610 --> 00:25:55,570
~ From now on, I’ll never let you slip away ~

258
00:25:55,600 --> 00:25:58,590
~ With every breath I take ~

259
00:25:59,420 --> 00:26:03,850
~ I’ll make up to you for the time we lost ~

260
00:26:30,230 --> 00:26:31,100
Sorry.

261
00:26:39,380 --> 00:26:40,430
Don’t say another word.

262
00:26:44,690 --> 00:26:49,990
~ As if the heavens saw my sorrow ~

263
00:26:50,250 --> 00:26:54,580
~ They guided us back to each other ~

264
00:26:54,990 --> 00:26:58,370
~ After the day we were suddenly torn apart ~

265
00:26:58,390 --> 00:27:03,100
~ They let me return to your side ~

266
00:27:03,420 --> 00:27:06,650
~ To know how much you mean to me ~

267
00:27:06,670 --> 00:27:10,030
~ And just how much I love you ~

268
00:27:10,640 --> 00:27:13,900
~ Since the moment of my return ~

269
00:27:13,930 --> 00:27:17,220
~ I realized I came back for you ~

270
00:27:17,250 --> 00:27:19,900
~ I’ve come back to make things right ~

271
00:27:19,930 --> 00:27:23,770
~ For the day I left you all alone ~

272
00:27:23,800 --> 00:27:30,700
~ From now on, I’ll never let you slip away ~

273
00:27:30,730 --> 00:27:33,990
~ With every breath I take ~

274
00:27:34,620 --> 00:27:39,160
~ I’ll make up to you for the time we lost ~

275
00:29:09,070 --> 00:29:09,990
P’ Le…

276
00:29:12,380 --> 00:29:13,390
It’s okay.

277
00:29:14,640 --> 00:29:15,730
It’s okay, Rann.

278
00:29:58,030 --> 00:30:00,740
~ I was blind to the truth ~

279
00:30:00,770 --> 00:30:02,840
~ Thinking it was for the best ~

280
00:30:03,980 --> 00:30:06,760
~ Only then did I find out about you ~

281
00:30:07,280 --> 00:30:09,990
~ Only then did I realize that you were gone ~

282
00:30:10,020 --> 00:30:15,290
~ As if the heavens saw my sorrow ~

283
00:30:15,560 --> 00:30:19,770
~ They guided us back to each other ~

284
00:30:16,920 --> 00:30:17,820
I'm sorry.

285
00:30:20,290 --> 00:30:23,580
~ After the day we were suddenly torn apart ~

286
00:30:23,610 --> 00:30:28,370
~ They let me return to your side ~

287
00:30:28,680 --> 00:30:31,920
~ To know how much you mean to me ~

288
00:30:31,950 --> 00:30:35,440
~ And just how much I love you ~

289
00:30:47,610 --> 00:30:49,270
- Could you take this for me?
- Of course.

290
00:31:06,680 --> 00:31:08,140
That was intense.

291
00:31:46,130 --> 00:31:47,740
We have a shareholders' meeting today.

292
00:31:48,540 --> 00:31:50,130
Those documents are very important.

293
00:31:50,650 --> 00:31:52,800
Make sure not a single one is missing.

294
00:31:53,960 --> 00:31:57,210
Are you… finally speaking to me again?

295
00:32:01,780 --> 00:32:02,830
Is the car ready?

296
00:32:06,010 --> 00:32:07,050
Everything is ready, Miss.

297
00:32:07,420 --> 00:32:10,370
Your humble servant has
the car waiting right out front.

298
00:32:10,660 --> 00:32:11,600
This way, please.

299
00:32:12,510 --> 00:32:15,940
I told you those documents are very important.

300
00:32:16,900 --> 00:32:17,820
Go get them.

301
00:32:21,770 --> 00:32:22,740
Certainly.

302
00:32:23,920 --> 00:32:25,800
- Here, let me take those.
- Thank you.

303
00:32:34,640 --> 00:32:35,970
And what I told you to prepare?

304
00:32:36,240 --> 00:32:37,470
It’s been taken care of.

305
00:32:40,200 --> 00:32:41,840
If you can’t handle high heels…

306
00:32:43,470 --> 00:32:44,570
then don’t wear them again.

307
00:32:45,000 --> 00:32:46,150
I can wear them.

308
00:32:48,620 --> 00:32:49,580
Suit yourself.

309
00:32:59,520 --> 00:33:00,510
Ow!

310
00:33:01,610 --> 00:33:04,980
Weren’t these supposed to be easy to wear?

311
00:33:05,600 --> 00:33:07,480
High heels are high heels after all.

312
00:33:08,330 --> 00:33:11,020
They’re killing my feet.
That seller was a total liar.

313
00:33:17,520 --> 00:33:18,370
Rann.

314
00:33:19,040 --> 00:33:21,430
Oh! P’ Le!

315
00:33:21,980 --> 00:33:25,540
You’re always doing that.
What if you make a hole in my cheek?

316
00:33:30,290 --> 00:33:33,560
If it leaves a hole,
then we’ll just have to plug it up.

317
00:33:46,170 --> 00:33:50,110
My shoes are rubbing me raw.
It hurts so bad.

318
00:33:51,150 --> 00:33:52,030
Oh no…

319
00:33:55,020 --> 00:33:56,730
Hey! P’ Le, what are you doing?

320
00:33:57,640 --> 00:33:58,650
Let me take a look.

321
00:34:06,850 --> 00:34:10,360
You don’t have to force
yourself to wear high heels, Rann.

322
00:34:22,340 --> 00:34:24,110
Next time, just tell me.

323
00:34:32,980 --> 00:34:36,730
I’ll stand still like a pillar
for you to lean on all night.

324
00:34:41,750 --> 00:34:43,719
I just wanted to look good,

325
00:34:44,889 --> 00:34:47,139
so I wouldn't embarrass you
when we’re side by side.

326
00:34:47,340 --> 00:34:49,290
Why do you care what people think?

327
00:34:50,580 --> 00:34:53,710
Just having you by my side like this…

328
00:34:55,239 --> 00:34:56,860
is enough to make me happy.

329
00:34:59,450 --> 00:35:01,400
Okay, Noo Rann?

330
00:35:07,780 --> 00:35:08,670
Really?

331
00:35:14,300 --> 00:35:15,580
Does it hurt much?

332
00:35:16,710 --> 00:35:17,590
Yeah.

333
00:35:19,760 --> 00:35:22,360
You used to tell me you’d
be the pillar I could lean on.

334
00:35:25,700 --> 00:35:26,820
Wait, Khun Rann.

335
00:35:27,530 --> 00:35:30,780
Please use these so your heels won’t hurt.

336
00:35:33,030 --> 00:35:34,060
Thank you.

337
00:35:35,500 --> 00:35:39,260
Don't thank me.
You should thank... someone else.

338
00:35:43,810 --> 00:35:44,600
Okay.

339
00:35:51,540 --> 00:35:54,560
I don’t get why you didn't just
give them to her yourself, Miss.

340
00:35:59,570 --> 00:36:02,250
If you're that worried about her,
why not give them to her yourself?

341
00:36:03,830 --> 00:36:04,750
Shut up.

342
00:36:05,660 --> 00:36:07,290
I still have a score to settle with you.

343
00:36:09,270 --> 00:36:10,860
What did I do to upset you this time?

344
00:36:11,180 --> 00:36:13,480
The scholarship.

345
00:36:14,150 --> 00:36:16,720
Oops. You caught me.

346
00:36:17,390 --> 00:36:19,410
But please have mercy on me, Khun Lené.

347
00:36:19,580 --> 00:36:23,090
I know way too many of your secrets.

348
00:36:24,690 --> 00:36:27,090
- Asshole.
- Ooh, such harsh words!

349
00:36:29,640 --> 00:36:34,080
How about being a little nicer
and going a bit easier on me?

350
00:36:35,770 --> 00:36:40,120
I know how much you love… this car.

351
00:36:40,890 --> 00:36:45,600
You even swapped the supercar you
bought last week for this one instead.

352
00:36:51,430 --> 00:36:54,530
Still can't choose?
You've been at it for a while now.

353
00:36:57,660 --> 00:36:58,850
In your opinion...

354
00:37:00,930 --> 00:37:03,040
which car is easiest to step out of?

355
00:37:04,400 --> 00:37:05,880
Are you choosing a car or a person?

356
00:37:10,500 --> 00:37:12,550
Hey, does this look nice?

357
00:37:13,520 --> 00:37:15,010
I’m making a vision board.

358
00:37:15,350 --> 00:37:17,220
I read it in a book.

359
00:37:17,410 --> 00:37:19,340
It says that if you want something in life,

360
00:37:19,360 --> 00:37:23,330
you should write it down or put
it somewhere you’ll see it often.

361
00:37:23,700 --> 00:37:24,950
And it’ll come true.

362
00:37:27,610 --> 00:37:32,140
For example, I want a small, cozy home.

363
00:37:33,030 --> 00:37:36,570
Or like how I want to study
in England after graduation.

364
00:37:37,220 --> 00:37:39,110
I’ve been adding pictures of that too.

365
00:37:39,570 --> 00:37:43,220
And I’m going to set it as my
wallpaper so I’ll see it all the time.

366
00:37:46,380 --> 00:37:48,480
- Quite the dreamer, aren't you?
- Hey!

367
00:37:50,060 --> 00:37:52,150
It doesn't hurt to try.

368
00:37:53,300 --> 00:37:55,680
And you, P’ Le?
Isn't there anything you want?

369
00:38:02,560 --> 00:38:03,680
I already have everything.

370
00:38:04,650 --> 00:38:08,630
I have a house, and a job waiting for me.

371
00:38:09,320 --> 00:38:11,500
As for a car… I'll go with a sports car.

372
00:38:11,960 --> 00:38:12,920
Much cooler.

373
00:38:14,310 --> 00:38:19,820
Okay, I get it. You're like, super rich.

374
00:38:24,010 --> 00:38:29,880
But if you’re living alone in a house
this small, why do you want a car this big?

375
00:38:36,610 --> 00:38:41,940
I once told my grandma that
after I graduate and get a job,

376
00:38:42,910 --> 00:38:46,920
I'll buy a big car so I can drive her everywhere.

377
00:38:48,670 --> 00:38:51,390
I guess it's something I've held onto.

378
00:38:57,070 --> 00:39:00,760
Then once you can buy it,
I’ll let you drive me around instead.

379
00:39:01,060 --> 00:39:01,930
Really?!

380
00:39:02,870 --> 00:39:04,150
No taking it back now.

381
00:39:06,680 --> 00:39:10,560
In that case, I'm adding your
photo to the board right away.

382
00:39:12,080 --> 00:39:13,300
Should I put it here?

383
00:39:16,390 --> 00:39:17,250
Am I right?

384
00:39:18,950 --> 00:39:22,540
One more word out of you...
and I’m replacing the driver.

385
00:39:34,220 --> 00:39:35,700
Sorry to keep you waiting.

386
00:39:35,730 --> 00:39:37,490
You’re right on time, Khun Rann.

387
00:39:38,430 --> 00:39:40,050
Isn't that right, Miss?

388
00:39:41,510 --> 00:39:42,330
Better get moving.

389
00:39:47,080 --> 00:39:48,170
Is this from last month?

390
00:39:48,950 --> 00:39:52,470
Check it for me.
If they confirm, tell me immediately.

391
00:39:54,710 --> 00:39:55,740
Hello, everyone.

392
00:39:57,710 --> 00:40:01,990
First of all, I’d like to thank
you all for joining us today.

393
00:40:03,150 --> 00:40:08,450
But before we get started, there’s
someone I’d like to introduce to you all.

394
00:40:33,970 --> 00:40:34,970
Hello, everyone.

395
00:40:35,910 --> 00:40:39,570
I’m Dean Dithakorn.
I look forward to working with you.

396
00:40:47,050 --> 00:40:49,480
I believe many of you are
already familiar with him.

397
00:40:49,660 --> 00:40:51,050
This is Khun Dean Dithakorn.

398
00:40:51,930 --> 00:40:55,810
He is an independent investor who
has decided to become a shareholder

399
00:40:56,310 --> 00:40:59,510
and help us develop our upcoming major projects.

400
00:41:01,260 --> 00:41:05,180
I hope everyone will give him a warm welcome.

401
00:41:07,750 --> 00:41:11,460
Sis, is a guy that handsome
really just an investor?

402
00:41:11,600 --> 00:41:14,410
He looks more like an angel
sent from heaven just for me.

403
00:41:14,430 --> 00:41:15,900
You’re so extra.

404
00:41:15,920 --> 00:41:19,480
He’s stunning from head to toe,
and dripping in designer brands.

405
00:41:19,510 --> 00:41:21,600
This is exactly the kind of
work environment I need.

406
00:41:22,120 --> 00:41:23,390
I'm obsessed!

407
00:41:24,430 --> 00:41:25,180
Lené.

408
00:41:27,180 --> 00:41:30,590
Khun Dean isn't familiar
with our organization yet.

409
00:41:31,760 --> 00:41:34,050
I’m counting on you to
look after him from now on.

410
00:41:39,090 --> 00:41:40,910
It’s a great honor, Khun Lené.

411
00:41:44,540 --> 00:41:45,930
I’ll give it my absolute best.

412
00:41:47,020 --> 00:41:48,030
I’m in your hands now.

413
00:41:58,260 --> 00:41:59,450
My pleasure.

414
00:42:00,610 --> 00:42:02,780
I’m so glad we meet again.

415
00:42:04,370 --> 00:42:08,490
I never imagined I'd get to work
with someone... this beautiful.

416
00:42:10,610 --> 00:42:14,370
I've been hearing so much about you.

417
00:42:14,430 --> 00:42:16,270
I hope it's all good things.

418
00:42:18,380 --> 00:42:19,710
There go our chances, Sis.

419
00:42:20,800 --> 00:42:24,770
I bet Khun Kanin is trying to set them up.

420
00:42:24,970 --> 00:42:28,700
They’re both so good-looking—
it’s a match made in heaven.

421
00:42:29,440 --> 00:42:30,930
So long, my darling.

422
00:42:31,190 --> 00:42:32,350
You’re so dramatic.

423
00:42:33,270 --> 00:42:34,780
I’m leaving Lené in your hands.

424
00:42:36,770 --> 00:42:38,260
I’ll take the very best care of her.

425
00:42:57,940 --> 00:42:58,830
Wait a second.

426
00:43:01,340 --> 00:43:05,430
I’m not sure if you remember, but
we met at my father’s birthday party.

427
00:43:08,180 --> 00:43:12,700
I don't really remember.
I attend quite a lot of functions.

428
00:43:14,770 --> 00:43:16,740
We can catch up another time then.

429
00:43:17,510 --> 00:43:19,930
I’m sure we’ll have plenty of time together.

430
00:43:20,940 --> 00:43:24,400
Anyway, please look after me, Khun Le.

431
00:43:25,380 --> 00:43:26,480
It’s Khun ‘Lené.’

432
00:43:29,610 --> 00:43:31,750
- And you are…?
- I’m Rann.

433
00:43:33,200 --> 00:43:36,170
Khun Rann. What a lovely name.

434
00:43:37,450 --> 00:43:39,810
I’m Dean. Nice to meet you.

435
00:43:40,930 --> 00:43:44,830
I’m sure you're far too busy to bother
getting to know a regular employee.

436
00:43:52,650 --> 00:43:54,250
I want a meeting summary.

437
00:43:55,500 --> 00:43:56,810
Certainly, Khun Lené.

438
00:43:58,690 --> 00:43:59,630
Now.

439
00:44:03,180 --> 00:44:03,850
Go.

440
00:44:08,560 --> 00:44:09,420
Right away.

441
00:44:19,830 --> 00:44:21,980
‘Khun Le’? Just ‘Khun Le’?

442
00:44:22,310 --> 00:44:24,690
Who gave him the right
to be so casual with her?

443
00:44:25,060 --> 00:44:27,810
‘We met before, remember?’
What, a trip down memory lane?

444
00:44:27,980 --> 00:44:29,820
Khun Rann. About that meeting earlier—

445
00:44:29,840 --> 00:44:32,090
Dream on. P’ Le already said
she doesn't remember him.

446
00:44:32,110 --> 00:44:33,790
The nerve, still trying to flirt with her.

447
00:44:36,240 --> 00:44:37,120
So annoying.

448
00:44:37,370 --> 00:44:39,340
And how could P’ Le
just let him call her that?

449
00:44:40,300 --> 00:44:41,850
‘Le’ belongs to me.

450
00:44:48,910 --> 00:44:50,820
That’s enough, Rann. Stop thinking.

451
00:44:55,840 --> 00:44:57,160
Dean Dithakorn.

452
00:44:58,300 --> 00:45:00,570
His name wasn’t in any
of the data I gathered.

453
00:45:02,350 --> 00:45:05,300
But he was at the funeral too.
How could you forget that, Rann?

454
00:45:11,940 --> 00:45:13,150
Dean Dithakorn.

455
00:45:14,090 --> 00:45:16,000
Famously known as 'The Silent Shark.'

456
00:45:16,030 --> 00:45:20,000
Orchestrates quiet yet powerful
deal, sending value to 10-year high.

457
00:45:21,380 --> 00:45:24,040
I bet Khun Kanin is trying to set them up.

458
00:45:24,070 --> 00:45:27,470
I never imagined I'd get to work
with someone this beautiful.

459
00:45:28,680 --> 00:45:29,470
Exaggerated.

460
00:45:35,810 --> 00:45:37,390
Trying to break the office computer?

461
00:45:40,070 --> 00:45:40,880
I’m not.

462
00:45:45,660 --> 00:45:46,670
What about Khun Dean?

463
00:45:54,430 --> 00:45:58,590
Why? Are you upset about something?

464
00:46:00,620 --> 00:46:01,630
Not at all.

465
00:46:03,170 --> 00:46:04,170
If you say so.

466
00:46:06,300 --> 00:46:07,870
You’re acting like you’re jealous.

467
00:46:21,980 --> 00:46:22,980
Hello.

468
00:46:24,880 --> 00:46:26,420
Is there something you need, Khun Pha?

469
00:46:32,980 --> 00:46:33,990
Have a seat.

470
00:46:34,380 --> 00:46:35,380
Thank you.

471
00:46:47,470 --> 00:46:49,850
Did you wish to see me
about something, Khun Kanin?

472
00:46:52,710 --> 00:46:55,210
Has there been anything
concerning about Le lately?

473
00:46:57,380 --> 00:46:59,010
It’s just as I’ve reported.

474
00:46:59,450 --> 00:47:03,820
Khun Lené is handling her work well,
and there’s nothing else to worry about.

475
00:47:11,720 --> 00:47:15,040
Or is there something
specific you'd like to know?

476
00:47:17,530 --> 00:47:21,260
If you think you've told me everything,
then I have nothing more to ask.

477
00:47:23,280 --> 00:47:24,140
Oh.

478
00:47:26,400 --> 00:47:29,060
What are your thoughts on Dean?

479
00:47:33,960 --> 00:47:35,840
I’m just an employee.

480
00:47:36,780 --> 00:47:40,020
It’s not my place to judge a shareholder.

481
00:47:41,770 --> 00:47:46,020
Come on. Just tell me what you think.

482
00:47:47,980 --> 00:47:50,410
At least from a woman's perspective.

483
00:47:53,870 --> 00:47:56,910
From what I know, he’s
a capable businessman.

484
00:47:57,100 --> 00:47:59,840
His connections could be a real asset to us.

485
00:48:00,860 --> 00:48:04,130
Having Khun Dean on board
is a great opportunity for us.

486
00:48:04,420 --> 00:48:08,740
As for anything else,
I can't really judge yet.

487
00:48:09,050 --> 00:48:10,450
I haven't worked with him before.

488
00:48:13,870 --> 00:48:16,680
You looked him up the moment
you knew who he was, didn't you?

489
00:48:18,940 --> 00:48:21,030
Good. You did well.

490
00:48:24,390 --> 00:48:27,550
But you still haven't answered me
from a woman's perspective.

491
00:48:30,440 --> 00:48:33,990
I want Dean to get close to Lené.

492
00:48:38,920 --> 00:48:41,150
You can help me bring them together, can't you?

493
00:48:51,160 --> 00:48:52,330
I'll do my best.

494
00:48:55,440 --> 00:48:58,450
Thanks. You can get back to work.

495
00:48:58,480 --> 00:48:59,480
Then I’ll take my leave.

496
00:49:00,180 --> 00:49:01,180
Sawasdee ka.

497
00:49:58,730 --> 00:49:59,530
What’s wrong?

498
00:50:01,140 --> 00:50:02,050
Nothing.

499
00:50:02,670 --> 00:50:05,620
Do you need something, Khun Lené?
I have work to do.

500
00:50:07,340 --> 00:50:08,590
Don’t tell me…

501
00:50:08,960 --> 00:50:09,940
What?

502
00:50:16,660 --> 00:50:17,670
You’re jealous.

503
00:50:21,570 --> 00:50:23,360
I’d better get back to work.

504
00:50:27,580 --> 00:50:28,550
I am not!

505
00:50:30,520 --> 00:50:31,740
Don't be so full of yourself.

506
00:50:32,560 --> 00:50:33,440
I’m not!

507
00:50:37,890 --> 00:50:40,330
Ugh! What on earth?!

508
00:50:49,500 --> 00:50:52,500
English Subtitles by Saowalak K.

509
00:50:53,020 --> 00:50:56,200
Khun Lené cheked the stock the other
day and found the goods we’d hidden.

510
00:50:56,660 --> 00:51:01,370
Do whatever it takes.
Make this shipment vanish from Lené’s sight.

511
00:51:01,510 --> 00:51:04,540
